Fill your kettle with plenty water and turn it on.
Take out your teapot, take off the lid and put in about 3 or 4 tea bags.
Depending on the size of your pot you may need more.
Pour the boiling water into the pot when your kettle has boiled.
Stir slightly.
Get a small jug, preferably one that matches your teapot if you have one, and fill it with milk.
Serve the sugar in a small sugar bowl.
Put a teaspoon in the sugar bowl.
Serve the tea, the milk and the sugar.
Bring out a cup and saucer for each person, and another teaspoon each.